org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.reasoner.implementation

Class Skolemization

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.reasoner.implementation.Skolemization

  • public class Skolemization
extends Object
    A class that implements skolemization and collision-free renaming of named nulls. The same name will always be renamed in the same way when using the same instance of Skolemization, but it is extremely unlikely that different names or different instances will ever produce the same name. This can be used to rename apart named nulls from different input sources to avoid clashes. There is also code for creating skolem constants with appropriate absolute IRIs.
    Author:
    Maximilian Marx

      • getRenamedNamedNull

        public RenamedNamedNull getRenamedNamedNull(String name)
        Creates a named null with a renamed name that is determined by the given original name. The result is a RenamedNamedNull to allow other code to recognise that no further renaming is necessary.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the NamedNull to be renamed here (or any other string for which to create a unique renaming)
        Returns:
        a RenamedNamedNull with a new name that is specific to this instance and name.

      • getSkolemConstant

        public AbstractConstant getSkolemConstant(NamedNull namedNull,
                                          TermFactory termFactory)
        Creates a skolem constant that is determined by the given NamedNull. The method ensures that a new unique name is generated unless the given object is already a RenamedNamedNull.
        Parameters:
        namedNull - the NamedNull to skolemize
        termFactory - the TermFactory that is used to create the constant
        Returns:
        a AbstractConstant with an IRI that is specific to this instance and namedNull.
